stylometry: The tradeoff/relationship between the two is simple when the demand goes up the price goes up, and when the demand goes down the price will go down.  We can use a graph to see where the best point will be to maxmize the profit.  We can do this by finding a happy medean between the price and demand.  We have to know that along with demand going up and down if the price is to high ther is going to be  a limited demand for it.  Same goes for low price if it is to low we may have a high demand but we are not going to have a high enough profit margin.  I would develope a graph and find the region that the price must be in to maximize profit, then go ahead and find that point of intersection where your going to make the most profit.
